From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 01:50:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] mmdevapi: Re-signal DualSense mono before ending render
 hotplug.

The render hotplug worker marks render_update_in_progress while it refreshes
endpoint state. Spider-Man Remastered can enumerate endpoints as soon as that
gate is released. If we wait until the following capture half of the hotplug
batch to re-signal the hidden logical DualSense mono endpoint, the game can
observe only the newly-created visible controller endpoint and miss the
restored logical endpoint it originally activated.

Re-signal the DualSense mono endpoint immediately after processing render
endpoint adds, before clearing render_update_in_progress. This keeps the
logical mono endpoint restoration ordered before any waiting render endpoint
enumeration can continue.
---
 dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c | 9 +++++----
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
index 99999999999..aaaaaaaaaaa 100644
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -1651,11 +1651,12 @@ static DWORD WINAPI update_thread_proc(void *user)
         add_endpoints_from_params(&params);
 
         if (params.flow == eRender)
-            InterlockedExchange(&render_update_in_progress, 0);
-
-        if (!params.more_data && InterlockedExchange(&dualsense_mono_render_add_pending, 0))
-            resignal_visible_dualsense_mono_endpoints();
+        {
+            if (InterlockedExchange(&dualsense_mono_render_add_pending, 0))
+                resignal_visible_dualsense_mono_endpoints();
+            InterlockedExchange(&render_update_in_progress, 0);
+        }
 
         if (params.more_data)
             params.flow = params.flow == eRender ? eCapture : eRender;
     }
